Automatic differentiation has a wide applications, which include real-parameter optimization, physical modeling, probabilistic inference, and neural networks.

Due to the computational cost of these tasks, it is necessary to implement a reliable and efficient differentiation utility.

This project examines current data (1950 to present) on overfishing and fishery collapse. We compare our results to findings in the Worm et al. (2006) paper which first reported on fishery collapse and its implications for biodiversity.

I explored the population of birds by examining three questions: Is the population of birds really declining, to what extent? If the answer to the first question is yes, is every famliy of birds encountering the same decline? What’s the effect of declining of birds on other related species?
We empirically explore why systematic and structural racism is interwined with urban ecological processes by investigating three cities: Birmingham, Baltimore and San Francisco.

A web app for visualizing personalized Spotify data. View your top artists, top tracks, recently played tracks, and detailed audio information about each track. Create and save new playlists of recommended tracks based on your existing playlists and more.
Custom WordPress theme and e-commerce site built with Timber and WooCommerce for blistabloc, a start-up selling the only reactive shoe insert that prevents blisters from forming.
R Project for my Data Science class at Northeastern to analyze the top Spotify tracks of 2017 and their audio features.
Facebook Messenger chat bot extension featuring authentication and full song streaming from within the Messenger app. Read more about it on The Verge.

Web app that allows people to crowdsource a party's music queue. Allows people to request songs, upvote songs, rate songs, etc. so the DJ can see how the crowd is feeling and queue songs accordingly. Won Best UI/UX Design at Hackbeanpot 2017.
Simple weather app made with Node.js, Express, and Heroku. Utilized the OpenWeatherMap API and Google Maps API.

Starry Station android app feature that provided users with the ability to easily filter content, pause the internet, and even create custom rules for blocking apps like Facebook and Twitter right from their phones.
Interactive holiday site for MullenLowe built around an algorithm that generated a holiday greeting to each and every person on the planet. Check out this short video describing the project.
